      • localize

        private void localize(boolean moveToOrigin)
        Attempts to set the odometer's angle to match the board's coordinates by rotating near a board corner. Uses the ultrasonic sensor to determine angles at which the walls are seen.
        Parameters:
        moveToOrigin - if true moves the robot to the line intersection nearest to the corner after calculating its position.

      • moveWhileAvoiding

        private boolean moveWhileAvoiding(Vector2 destination,
                        float positionTolerance,
                        boolean stopFacingObstacle)
        Moves the robot to a position while avoiding obstacles on the way.
        Parameters:
        destination - the destination point.
        positionTolerance - the distance under which the robot must be to the given position before returning.

      • moveUntilObstacle

        private boolean moveUntilObstacle(Vector2 destination)
        Tries to move the robot to a given position, but stops if an obstacle is encountered.
        Parameters:
        destination - the destination point.

      • getTimeRemaining

        Gets the time remaining in the match.

      • blockSearch

        private boolean blockSearch(float searchDirection,
                  float searchWidth)
        Sweeps an arc and moves to the first object seen.
        Parameters:
        searchDirection - the direction in degrees that the robot will center the sweep around.
        searchWidth - how many degrees the sweep will cover.
        Returns:
        true if the robot has approached a block.
